  "texts": [
    "Since the terminal state is absorbing, we have P (s i+1 = ⊥ | ⊥, a i) = 1 (i.e., once the conversation ends, it does not restart).",
    "Embedded within P (s i+1 | s i, a i), there are two steps of randomness: first, the transition to m i (how the business actually responds after observing suggestion a i); and second, the transition to c i+1, o i+1 (how the customer responds to the business's message m i).",
    "effect of ai on business's mi",
    "The above decomposition is shown primarily to distinguish our suggested response model to existing works in the multi-turn interactions literature where a chatbot operates autonomously.",
    "Our work introduces the additional consideration of P (m i | s i, a i), where the SR agent needs to learn how a i impacts the business's response m i."
